#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:169
#, no-wrap
msgid "Faster than starting with stage1"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:173
#, no-wrap
msgid "You can still tweak your settings"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:177
#, no-wrap
msgid "You cannot tweak as much as with a stage1"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:181
#, no-wrap
msgid "It's not the fastest way to install Gentoo"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:185
#, no-wrap
msgid "You have to accept the optimizations we chose for the bootstrap"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:196
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Choosing to go with a <e>stage3</e> allows for the fastest install of Gentoo\n"
"Linux, but also means that your base system will have the optimization\n"
"settings that we chose for you (which to be honest, are good settings\n"
"and were carefully chosen to enhance performance while maintaining\n"
"stability). <e>stage3</e> is also required if you want to install Gentoo using\n"
"prebuilt packages or without a network connection.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><th>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:206
#, no-wrap
msgid "Stage3"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:211
#, no-wrap
msgid "Fastest way to get a Gentoo base system"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:215
#, no-wrap
msgid "Suitable for networkless installations"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:219
#, no-wrap
msgid "You cannot tweak the base system - it's built already"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:223
#, no-wrap
msgid "You cannot brag about having used stage1 or stage2"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:228
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Write down (or remember) what stage you want to use. You need this later when\n"
"you decide what LiveCD (or other installation medium) you want to use. You might\n"
"be interested to know that, if you decide to use different optimization settings\n"
"after having installed Gentoo, you will be able to recompile your entire system\n"
"with the new optimization settings.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:236
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now take a look at the available installation media.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:246
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <e>Gentoo Alpha LiveCD</e> is a bootable CD which contain a\n"
"self-sustained Gentoo environment. It allows you to boot Linux from the CD.\n"
"During the boot process your hardware is detected and the appropriate drivers\n"
"are loaded. It is maintained by Gentoo developers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:253
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <e>Gentoo Alpha LiveCD</e> is a small, no-nonsense, bootable CD which sole \n"
"purpose is to boot the system, prepare the networking and continue with the \n"
"Gentoo installation. It does not contain any stages (or, in some cases, a \n"
"single stage1 file), source code or precompiled packages. For example the \n"
"alpha variant of this LiveCD can be found in the \n"
"<path>releases/1.4_rc1/alpha</path> subdirectory and is called\n"
"<c>gentoo-alpha-1.4rc1-test3.iso.bz2</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:266
#, no-wrap
msgid "Download, Burn and Boot the Gentoo LiveCD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:268
#, no-wrap
msgid "Downloading and Burning the LiveCDs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:272
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You have chosen to use a Gentoo LiveCD (if not, then you are reading the\n"
"wrong document). We'll first start by downloading and burning the chosen\n"
"LiveCD. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:278
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Visit one of our <uri\n"
"link=\"/main/en/mirrors.xml\">mirrors</uri> and go to\n"
"<path>releases/1.4rc1/alpha</path> which is where the LiveCD(s) of your choice \n"
"are located. Inside that directory you'll find so-called ISO-files. Those are \n"
"full CD images which you can write on a CD-R.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:286
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In case you wonder if your downloaded file is corrupted or not, you can\n"
"check its MD5 checksum and compare it with the MD5 checksum we provide (such as\n"
"<path>gentoo-alpha-1.4rc1-test3.iso.bz2.md5sum</path>). You can check the MD5 \n"
"checksum with the <c>md5sum</c> tool under Linux/Unix or <uri\n"
"link=\"http://www.etree.org/md5com.html\">md5sum</uri> for Windows.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:294
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Once downloaded, decompress the ISO file (as it is stored in a compressed format\n"
"using the Burrows-Wheeler text compression algorithm) using <c>bunzip2</c> (on\n"
"Unix/Linux systems):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:299
#, no-wrap
msgid "Decompressing the iso.bz2 file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:300
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>bunzip2 gentoo-alpha-1.4rc1-test3.iso.bz2</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:304
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Another way to check the validity of the downloaded file is to use GnuPG to\n"
"verify the cryptographic signature that we provide (the file ending with\n"
"<path>.asc</path>). Download the signature file and obtain the public key:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:309
#, no-wrap
msgid "Obtaining the public key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:310
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>gpg --keyserver pgp.mit.edu --recv-keys 17072058</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:314
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now verify the signature:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:317
#, no-wrap
msgid "Verify the cryptographic signature"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:318
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>gpg --verify &lt;signature file&gt; &lt;downloaded iso&gt;</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:322
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To burn the downloaded ISO(s), you have to select raw-burning. How you\n"
"do this is highly program-dependent. We will discuss <c>cdrecord</c> and\n"
"<c>K3B</c> here; more information can be found in our <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/faq.xml#isoburning\">Gentoo FAQ</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:330
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    With cdrecord, you simply type <c>cdrecord dev=/dev/hdc</c> (replace\n"
"    <path>/dev/hdc</path> with your CD-RW drive's device path) followed\n"
"    by the path to the ISO file :)\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:335
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    With K3B, select <c>Tools</c> &gt; <c>CD</c> &gt; <c>Burn Image</c>. Then\n"
"    you can locate your ISO file within the 'Image to Burn' area. Finally click\n"
"    <c>Start</c>.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:344
#, no-wrap
msgid "Booting the Alpha LiveCD(s)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:348
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When your Alpha is powered on, the first thing that gets started is the\n"
"firmware. It is loosely synonymous with the BIOS software on PC systems. There\n"
"are two types of firmware on Alpha systems: SRM (<e>Systems Reference \n"
"Manual</e>) and ARC (<e>Advanced Risc Console</e>).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:355
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"SRM is based on the Alpha Console Subsystem specification, which provides an\n"
"operating environment for OpenVMS, Tru64 UNIX, and Linux operating systems. ARM\n"
"is based on the Advanced RISC Computing (ARC) specification, which provides\n"
"an operating environment for Windows NT.  You can find a \n"
"<uri link=\"http://www.alphalinux.org/faq/SRM-HOWTO/\">detailed guide</uri> on \n"
"using SRM over at the Alpha Linux website.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:364
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If your Alpha system supports both SRC and ARCs (ARC, AlphaBIOS, ARCSBIOS) you\n"
"should follow <uri link=\"http://www.alphalinux.org/faq/x31.html\">these\n"
"instructions</uri> for switching to SRM. If your system already uses SRM, you\n"
"are all set. If your system can only use ARCs (Ruffian, nautilus, xl, etc.) you\n"
"will need to choose <c>MILO</c> later on when we are talking about bootloaders.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:372
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now to boot an Alpha LiveCD, put the CD-ROM in the tray and reboot the system.\n"
"You can use SRM to boot the LiveCD. If you cannot do that, you will have to use\n"
"<c>MILO</c>. If you don't have <c>MILO</c> installed already, use one of the\n"
"precompiled <c>MILO</c> images available on <uri\n"
"link=\"http://dev.gentoo.org/~taviso/milo/\">taviso's homepage</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:379
#, no-wrap
msgid "Booting a CD-ROM using SRM"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:380
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(List available hardware drives)</comment>\n"
"&gt;&gt;&gt; <i>show device</i>\n"
"dkb0.0.1.4.0        DKB0       TOSHIBA CDROM\n"
"<comment>(...)</comment>\n"
"<comment>(Substitute dkb0 with your CD-ROM drive device)</comment>\n"
"&gt;&gt;&gt; <i>boot dkb0 -flags 0</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:388
#, no-wrap
msgid "Booting a CD-ROM using MILO"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:389
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(Substitute hdb with your CD-ROM drive device)</comment>\n"
"MILO&gt; <i>boot hdb:boot/vmlinuz initrd=initrd.img root=/dev/ram0 init=/linuxrc</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:394
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You should have a root (\"#\") prompt on the current console and can also switch\n"
"to other consoles by pressing Alt-F2, Alt-F3 and Alt-F4. Get back to the one you\n"
"started on by pressing Alt-F1.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:400
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now continue with <uri link=\"#hardware\">Extra Hardware Configuration</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:406
#, no-wrap
msgid "Extra Hardware Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:410
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When the Live CD boots, it tries to detect all your hardware devices and\n"
"loads the appropriate kernel modules to support your hardware. In the\n"
"vast majority of cases, it does a very good job. However, in some cases (the\n"
"SPARC LiveCDs don't even do autodetection), it may not auto-load the kernel \n"
"modules you need. If the PCI auto-detection missed some of your system's \n"
"hardware, you will have to load the appropriate kernel modules manually. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:419
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In the next example we try to load the <c>8139too</c> module (support for \n"
"certain kinds of network interfaces):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:423
#, no-wrap
msgid "Loading kernel modules"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:424
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>modprobe 8139too</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:430
#, no-wrap
msgid "Optional: Tweaking Hard Disk Performance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:434
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you are an advanced user, you might want to tweak the IDE hard disk\n"
"performance using <c>hdparm</c>. With the <c>-tT</c> options you can\n"
"test the performance of your disk (execute it several times to get a\n"
"more precise impression):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:440
#, no-wrap
msgid "Testing disk performance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:441
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>hdparm -tT /dev/hda</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:445
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To tweak, you can use any of the following examples (or experiment\n"
"yourself) which use <path>/dev/hda</path> as disk (substitute with your\n"
"disk):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:450
#, no-wrap
msgid "Tweaking hard disk performance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:451
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>Activate DMA:</comment>                                       # <i>hdparm -d 1 /dev/hda</i>\n"
"<comment>Activate DMA + Safe Performance-enhancing Options:</comment>  # <i>hdparm -d 1 -A 1 -m 16 -u 1 -a 64 /dev/hda</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:458
#, no-wrap
msgid "Optional: User Accounts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:462
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you plan on giving other people access to your installation\n"
"environment or you want to chat using <c>irssi</c> without root privileges (for\n"
"security reasons), you need to create the necessary user accounts and change \n"
"the root password.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:469
#, no-wrap
msgid "To change the root password, use the <c>passwd</c> utility:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:472
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing the root password"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:473
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>passwd</i>\n"
"New password: <comment>(Enter your new password)</comment>\n"
"Re-enter password: <comment>(Re-enter your password)</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:479
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To create a user account, we first enter their credentials, followed by\n"
"its password. We use <c>useradd</c> and <c>passwd</c> for these tasks.\n"
"In the next example, we create a user called &quot;john&quot;.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:484
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a user account"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:485
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>useradd -m -G users john</i>\n"
"# <i>passwd john</i>\n"
"New password: <comment>(Enter john's password)</comment>\n"
"Re-enter password: <comment>(Re-enter john's password)</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:492
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can change your user id from root to the newly created user by using\n"
"<c>su</c>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:496
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing user id"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:497
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>su - john</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:503
#, no-wrap
msgid "Optional: Viewing Documentation while Installing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:507
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you want to view the Gentoo Handbook (either from-CD or online) during the\n"
"installation, make sure you have created a user account (see <uri\n"
"link=\"#useraccounts\">Optional: User Accounts</uri>). Then press <c>Alt-F2</c> to\n"
"go to a new terminal and log in.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:514
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you want to view the documentation on the CD you can immediately run\n"
"<c>lynx</c> to read it:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:518
#, no-wrap
msgid "Viewing the on-CD documentation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:519
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>lynx /mnt/cdrom/docs/html/index.html</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:523
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"However, it is preferred that you use the online Gentoo Handbook as it will be\n"
"more recent than the one provided on the CD. You can view it using <c>lynx</c>\n"
"as well, but only after having completed the <e>Configuring your Network</e>\n"
"chapter (otherwise you won't be able to go on the Internet to view the\n"
"document):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:530
#, no-wrap
msgid "Viewing the Online Documentation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:531
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>lynx http://www.gentoo.org/doc/en/handbook/handbook-alpha.xml</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:535
#, no-wrap
msgid "You can go back to your original terminal by pressing <c>Alt-F1</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:541
#, no-wrap
msgid "Optional: Starting the SSH Daemon"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:545
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you want to allow other users to access your computer during the\n"
"Gentoo installation (perhaps because those users are going to help you\n"
"install Gentoo, or even do it for you), you need to create a user\n"
"account for them and perhaps even provide them with your root password \n"
"(<e>only</e> do that <e>if</e> you <b>fully trust</b> that user).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:553
#, no-wrap
msgid "To fire up the SSH daemon, execute the following command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:556
#, no-wrap
msgid "Starting the SSH daemon"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:557
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>/etc/init.d/sshd start</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-alpha-medium.xml:561
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To be able to use sshd, you first need to set up your networking. Continue with\n"
"the chapter on <uri link=\"?part=1&amp;chap=3\">Configuring your Network</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""
